d\"\n|-\n| 2011\u20132015\n| ''[[Jessie (2011 TV series)|Jessie]]''\n| Emma Ross\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''{{sortname|The|Dog Who Saved the Holidays|nolink=1}}''\n| Eve\n| Voice role; television film\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Austin & Ally]]''\n| Emma Ross\n| Episode: \"[[Austin & Jessie & Ally All Star New Year]]\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''{{sortname|A|Sister's Nightmare|nolink=1}}''\n| Emily Ryder\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2013\u20132014\n| ''[[Pass the Plate]]''\n| Herself\n| Co-host; seasons 3\u20134\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[I Didn't Do It (TV series)|I Didn't Do It]]''\n| Sherri\n| Episode: \"Dance Fever\"\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Ultimate Spider-Man (TV series)|Ultimate Spider-Man]]''\n| Emma Ross\n| Voice role; episode: \"Halloween Night at the Museum\"\n|-\n| 2015\u20132018\n| ''[[Bunk'd]]''\n| Emma Ross\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[K.C. Undercover]]''\n| Emma <!-- credited in the episode as just \"Emma\" with no last name -->\n| Episode: \"All Howl's Eve\"\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[The Swap (2016 film)|The Swap]]''\n| Ellie O'Brien\n| [[List of Disney Channel original films#Disney Channel Original Movies|Disney Channel Original Movie]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/04/disney-channel-original-movie-the-swap-dcom-marathon-1201741163|title=Disney Channel Original Movie \u2018The Swap\u2019 Set As Network Plans 100-Pic Celebration|first=Patrick|last=Hipes|date=April 20, 2016|access-date=August 7, 2018|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Happy Together (2018 TV series)|Happy Together]]''\n| Sierra\n| Episode: Pilot<ref>{{cite web|url=https://headlineplanet.com/home/2018/07/30/first-look-peyton-list-guest-stars-happy-together-pilot-harry-styles-executive-producer/|title=First Look: Peyton List Guest Stars In \"Happy Together\" Pilot; Harry Styles Is An Executive Producer|work=Headline Planet|first=Brian|last=Cantor|date=July 31, 2018|access-date=August 13, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018-2019\n| ''[[Light as a Feather (TV series)|Light as a Feather]]''\n| Olivia Richmond\n| Main role (season 1), Guest (season 2)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/light-as-a-feather-cast-liana-liberato-haley-ramm-peyton-list-hulu-awesomenesstv-1202403357/|title='Light As A Feather' Cast Set: Liana Liberato, Haley Ramm, Peyton List, Others Join Hulu & AwesomenessTV Drama|work=Deadline|first=Erik|last=Pedersen|date=June 4, 2018|access-date=August 7, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Project Runway All Stars]]''\n| Herself (Guest Judge)\n| Season 7, Episode 5<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mylifetime.com/shows/project-runway-all-stars/season-7/episode-5|title=Watch Of     On The Prowl  Full Episode - Project Runway All Stars - Lifetime|publisher=}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Cobra Kai (TV series)|Cobra Kai]]''\n| Tory\n| Recurring role<ref name=\"CobraKaiS2\">{{cite web |last1=Petski |first1=Denise |title=\u2018Cobra Kai\u2019: Peyton List To Recur In Season 2 Of YouTube Series |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/cobra-kai-peyton-list-recur-season-2-youtube-series-1202490072/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=October 26, 2018 |date=October 26, 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Music video appearances\n! Year\n! Title\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Artist\n|-\n| 2018\n| \"[[Only You (Cheat Codes and Little Mix song)|Only You]]\"\n| [[Cheat Codes (DJs)|Cheat Codes]] and [[Little Mix]]<ref>{{cite web |first=Sofia |last=Mele |title=Cheat Codes and Little Mix Tell a Mermaid Love Story in Vibrant 'Only You' Video: Watch |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8465364/cheat-codes-little-mix-video-only-you |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=July 13, 2018 |accessdate=July 13, 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n!Year\n!Award\n!Category\n!Work\n!Result\n!Ref.\n|-\n|[[34th Young Artist Awards|2013]]\n|Young Artist Award\n|Best Performance in a Feature Film \u2013 Young Ensemble Cast\n<small>(with [[Zachary Gordon]], [[Robert Capron]], [[Peyton List (actress, born 1998)|Peyton List]], [[Laine MacNeil]]</small>\n<small>[[Connor & Owen Fielding]], [[Devon Bostick]] and [[Grayson Russell]])</small>\n|''Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Dog Days''\n|{{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"YoungArtistAwards_3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms34.html|title=34th Annual Young Artist Awards|work=YoungArtistAwards.org|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6FaZ1wnUQ?url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms34.html|archivedate=April 2, 2013|url-status=dead|accessdate=March 31, 2013}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Peyton Roi List}}\n<!-- EDITORS: Please DO NOT add site links that could be considered advertisements for commercial gain. Repeated violations constitute spamming, and are considered vandalism. -->\n* {{IMDb name|2572554|Peyton List}}\n* {{Twitter}}<!-- only site controlled by subject so is \"official site\" per ELNO exception -->\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List, Peyton Roi}}\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Florida]]\n[[Category:Actresses from New York City]]\n[[Category:American child actresses]]\n[[Category:American child models]]\n[[Category:American female models]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Fraternal twin actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Twin people from the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{short description|American actress and model}}\n{{For|the actress from ''[[FlashForward]]'' and ''[[Mad Men]]''|Peyton List (actress, born 1986<!--This refers to another actress - please don't change the year-->)}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Peyton List\n| image              = Peyton Roi List.JPG\n| alt                = Portrait image of Peyton List\n| caption            = List in 2013\n| birth_name         = Peyton Roi List\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1998|4|6}}\n| birth_place        = [[Florida]], U.S.\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n* Actress\n* model\n<!-- Please DO NOT list \"singer\" unless/until she meets the notability guidelines for that, per WP:NSINGER -->\n}}\n| years_active       = 2002\u2013present\n| relatives          = [[Spencer List]] (twin brother)\n}}\n\n'''Peyton Roi List'''<ref name=\"Hollywood.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywood.com/celebrities/peyton-roi-list-58405847/ |title=Peyton Roi List |website=Hollywood.com |accessdate=June 15, 2018 |archivedate=August 14, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160814164943/http://www.hollywood.com/celebrities/peyton-roi-list-58405847/ |url-status=dead}}</ref> (born April 6, 1998<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900077&type=list|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120616173906/http://www.disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=900077&type=list|title=Peyton List|work=[[Disney Channel]]|archivedate=June 16, 2012|accessdate=May 9, 2015}}</ref>) is an American actress and model. List began her career as a child model, modeling for [[tween]] magazines and companies. She made her acting debut with the film ''[[27 Dresses]]'' (2008), and soon became recognized for playing [[Greg Heffley#Holly Hills|Holly Hills]] in the [[Diary of a Wimpy Kid (film series)|''Diary of a Wimpy Kid'' film series]]. \n\nList rose to international attention for portraying Emma Ross on the [[Disney Channel]] series ''[[Jessie (2011 TV series)|Jessie]]'' (2011\u20132015), the eldest of four siblings that are being cared for by a young nanny, a role which she reprised in the spinoff series ''[[Bunk'd]]'' (2015\u20132018). She has since starred as Olivia Richmond on the [[Hulu]] [[web series]] [[Light as a Feather (TV series)|''Light as a Feather'']] (2018), and portrayed [[List of The Karate Kid characters#Tory|Tory]] in the [[YouTube Premium]] series ''[[Cobra Kai]]'' (2019). \n\nList's other works in film include starring in [[Remember Me (2010 film)|''Remember Me'']] (2010), [[The Sorcerer's Apprentice (2010 film)|''The Sorcerer's Apprentice'']] (2010), [[Bereavement (film)|''Bereavement'']] (2010), [[Something Borrowed (film)|''Something Borrowed'']] (2011), ''[[The Seventh Dwarf]]'' (2014), ''[[The Thinning]]'' (2016), [[The Outcasts (2017 film)|''The Outcasts'']] (2017), and ''[[The Thinning: New World Order]]'' (2018). List has also appeared in the [[Television film|television films]] ''[[Secrets in the Walls]]'' (2010) and [[The Swap (2016 film)|''The Swap'']] (2016).\n\n==Early life==\nList was born April 6, 1998.<ref name=\"Hollywood.com\"/> She has two brothers, her twin [[Spencer List|Spencer]],<ref name=TribuneChronicle>{{cite web|first = Andy | last = Gray | newspaper = [[Tribune Chronicle]] |url=http://www.tribtoday.com/page/content.detail/id/554977/Peyton-List-is-no-wimpy-kid.html|title=Peyton List is no wimpy kid | location = Warren, Ohio |date=March 28, 2011 |accessdate=June 15, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150712143223/http://www.tribtoday.com/page/content.detail/id/554977/Peyton-List-is-no-wimpy-kid.html|archivedate=July 12, 2015|url-status=dead|url-access=subscription }}</ref> and a younger brother,<ref name=TeenVogue>Keiser, Amanda. [http://www.teenvogue.com/gallery/peyton-list-room-makeover#7 \"Peyton List Just Got the Ultimate Room Makeover and We Have the Exclusive First Look!\"]. ''[[Teen Vogue]]''. Retrieved May 2, 2017.</ref> Phoenix, both of whom are actors.<ref name=TribuneChronicle/>\n\nShe attended The Carroll School (P.S. 58) for elementary school, and the New Voices School for Academic and Creative Arts (M.S. 443) for middle school, both in [[New York City]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lo|first1=Danica|title=Peyton List's Favorite New York City Hotspots|url=http://www.epicurious.com/archive/blogs/editor/2014/07/peyton-list-new-york-city.html|website=The Epicurious Blog|publisher=Conde Nast|accessdate=June 1, 2016}}</ref> She attended [[Oak Park High School (California)|Oak Park High School]] in [[Oak Park, California]], where she graduated in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kowalski|first1=Kristine Hope|title=Class of 2016: Spencer and Peyton List Graduate High School|url=http://www.twistmagazine.com/posts/spencer-peyton-list-graduate-high-school-103529/photos/peyton-spencer-list-146083|website=Twist Magazine|publisher=Bauer Teen Group|accessdate=June 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n[[File:Peyton_R._List_at_27_Dresses_Premiere_1.jpg|right|thumb|Upright|List at the ''[[27 Dresses]]'' premiere in January 2008]]\nList first began her career as a child model, and in 2009 appeared on the cover of the ''[[American Girl (magazine)|American Girl]]'''s 2009 Back to School issue. In 2011, she modeled for [[Tween Brands|''Justice'' magazine]]. She had also appeared in over four hundred advertisements in various formats for various companies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kontrolgirl.com/2013/03/14/introducing-the-spring-issue-of-kontrol-girl-magazine-featuring-peyton-list-mindless-behavior/|title=Introducing... The Spring Issue of Kontrol Girl Magazine Featuring Peyton List & Mindless Behavior!|date=March 14, 2013|work=Kontrol Girl magazine|accessdate=September 30, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://rockycoastnews.blogspot.com/2012/01/meet-insider-raising-actress.html|title=Rocky Coast News: MEET INSIDER: Raising Actress & Fashionable Peyton List|last=Mills|first=David|date=January 21, 2012|work=Meet Insider&nbsp;\u2013 Rocky Coast News|location=Maine|accessdate=September 30, 2013}}</ref>\n\nList first began acting with television and film appearances. She first made an uncredited appearance on the [[soap opera]] ''[[As the World Turns]]'' in 2002.<ref name=\":0\" /> In 2004, she appeared on the television show ''[[All My Children]]'' as Bess, and in the same year made a cameo appearance in the feature film ''[[Spider-Man 2]]'', which went uncredited.<ref name=\":1\" /> In 2008, she appeared in the feature film ''[[27 Dresses]]'', starring as the young version of the character Jane Nichols. The film was a commercial success,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl1229030913/?landingModalImageUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fm.media-amazon.com%2Fimages%2FG%2F01%2FIMDbPro%2Fimages%2Fhome%2FwelcomeToBomojov2._CB1571421611_.png|title=27 Dresses|website=Box Office Mojo|access-date=2019-11-20}}</ref> and served as her acting debut. \n\nList began to appear in more feature films, and in 2010 was cast alongside [[Robert Pattinson]] in the film ''[[Remember Me (2010 film)|Remember Me]]'' as Samantha, a girl who bullies Pattinson's character's little sister. The film was a box-office success.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl2859304449/?landingModalImageUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fm.media-amazon.com%2Fimages%2FG%2F01%2FIMDbPro%2Fimages%2Fhome%2FwelcomeToBomojov2._CB1571421611_.png|title=Remember Me|website=Box Office Mojo|access-date=2019-11-20}}</ref> In the same year, List had begun her work with [[Disney]], and appeared as the younger version of Becky in the [[fantasy]] film ''[[The Sorcerer's Apprentice (2010 film)|The Sorcerer's Apprentice]]'', which turned to be a financial failure.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl2540733953/?landingModalImageUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fm.media-amazon.com%2Fimages%2FG%2F01%2FIMDbPro%2Fimages%2Fhome%2FwelcomeToBomojov2._CB1571421611_.png|title=The Sorcerer's Apprentice|website=Box Office Mojo|access-date=2019-11-20}}</ref> She also was cast in the [[Lifetime Movie Network|Lifetime]] [[television film]] ''[[Secrets in the Walls]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mediamikes.com/2011/09/dvd-review-secrets-in-the-walls/|title=DVD Review \"Secrets in the Walls\"|date=2011-09-11|website=MediaMikes|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> and played Wendy Miller in the [[Crime fiction|crime]] [[Horror film|horror]] film [[Bereavement (film)|Bereavement]], which was a [[Box office|box-office]] success.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl2554627585/|title=Bereavement|website=Box Office Mojo|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, List starred as [[List of Diary of a Wimpy Kid characters|Holly Hills]], the crush of [[Greg Heffley]], in the [[comedy]] film ''[[Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Rodrick Rules (film)|Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Rodrick Rules]]'', the second installment of the [[Diary of a Wimpy Kid (film series)|Diary of a Wimpy Kid film series]]. The film performed well commercially,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/article/ed3531342852/|title=Weekend Report: 'Wimpy Kid' Blindsides 'Sucker Punch'|website=Box Office Mojo|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> and List later reprised her role for its sequel, ''[[Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Dog Days (film)|Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Dog Days]]''. The film was a success alike to its prequels, and the acting ensemble, including List, had won a [[Young Artist Award]].<ref name=\"YoungArtistAwards_3\" /> List next had a role in the [[romantic comedy]] film [[Something Borrowed (film)|''Something Borrowed'']] in 2011,<ref>{{Citation|title=Something Borrowed (2011)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/something_borrowed_2011|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> which was received negatively.\n[[File:Jessie Cast.jpg|left|thumb|The cast of ''[[Jessie (2011 TV series)|Jessie]]'' in 2011|alt=]]In 2011, List began her work on [[Disney Channel]], and was cast as Emma Ross, the eldest of four affluent children, on the Disney Channel series ''[[Jessie (2011 TV series)|Jessie]]'' alongside [[Debby Ryan]] and her ''Diary of a Wimpy Kid'' co-star [[Karan Brar]]. The show attained millions of viewers on average per episode,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-25-friday-cable-originals-11-28-2014.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY\u2019s Top 25 Friday Cable Originals (& Network Update): 11.28.2014 {{!}} Showbuzz Daily|website=www.showbuzzdaily.com|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> and soon became List's biggest role at the time. The show ran for four seasons, and ended on February 25, 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/02/jessie-cancelled-spinoff-peyton-list-karan-brar-skai-jackson-disney-channel-1201380940/|title=Disney Channel\u2019s \u2018Jessie\u2019 Ending Run, But Spinoff Series Set With Stars Peyton List, Karan Brar & Skai Jackson|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|last2=Andreeva|first2=Nellie|date=2015-02-25|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> At the same time, it was announced that List, along with Brar and [[Skai Jackson]], would reprise their roles in the spinoff series ''[[Bunk'd]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |url=https://deadline.com/2015/02/jessie-cancelled-spinoff-peyton-list-karan-brar-skai-jackson-disney-channel-1201380940/ |title=Disney Channel's 'Jessie' Ending Run, But Spinoff Series Set With Stars Peyton List, Karan Brar & Skai Jackson |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=February 25, 2015 |accessdate=February 25, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/jessie-ending-debby-ryan-peyton-list-spinoff|title=Exclusive! 'Jessie' Is Ending, but Don't Worry\u2014There's a Spin-off Series on the Way|last=Firman|first=Tehrene|website=Teen Vogue|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> The show began airing in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2015/04/24/jessie-spinoff-bunkd-peyton-list-skai-jackson-karan-brar/|title=Disney Channel's Jessie Spinoff Gets Title, Premise, Cast Additions|last=Mitovich|first=Matt Webb|last2=Mitovich|first2=Matt Webb|date=2015-04-24|website=TVLine|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> Along with reprising the role on Bunk'd, she also had appeared as Emma Ross on other Disney Channel shows, such as [[Austin & Ally|''Austin & All''y]] and [[I Didn't Do It (TV series)|''I Didn't Do It'']].\n\nAlong with her television work, List continued her work in films. In 2012, she appeared in the [[drama]] film ''[[The Trouble with Cali]]'', which was received negatively.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nepascene.com/2015/07/movie-review-trouble-with-cali-awful-people-say-why-should-see-it/|title=MOVIE REVIEW: 'The Trouble with Cali' is as awful as people say - which is why you should see it|date=2015-07-10|website=NEPA Scene|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> From 2013 to 2014, she co-hosted the Disney Channel program ''[[Pass the Plate]]'', a segment focusing on healthy eating,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110810224246/http://disneychannelmedianet.com/web/showpage/showpage.aspx?program_id=3114203&type=lead|title=Disney Channel Medianet|date=2011-08-10|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> with Karan Brar. In 2014, she voiced Princess Rose in the English dub of the German [[Animation|animated]] film ''[[The Seventh Dwarf]]''. Though the film was a moderate financial success,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/title/tt2914892/?ref_=bo_se_r_1|title=The Seventh Dwarf|website=Box Office Mojo|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> it was received unfavorably by critics.<ref>{{Citation|last=Filmstarts|title=Die Filmstarts-Kritik zu Der 7bte Zwerg|url=http://www.filmstarts.de/kritiken/208559/kritik.html|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> In 2015, List performed with [[Ingrid Michaelson]] at one of Michaelson's concerts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/hot-pics/those-pants-tho-2015126|title=Hot Pics!-Those Pants Tho!|work=Us Weekly|accessdate=August 9, 2015}}</ref> \n[[File:10.8.16PeytonListByLuigiNovi1.jpg|thumb|List in 2016]]\nIn 2016, List co-starred along with [[Jacob Bertrand]] in the [[Disney Channel Original Movie]] [[The Swap (2016 film)|''The Swap'']], appearing as Ellie O'Brien.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/04/disney-channel-original-movie-the-swap-dcom-marathon-1201741163/|title=Disney Channel Original Movie \u2018The Swap\u2019 Set As Network Plans 100-Pic Celebration|last=Hipes|first=Patrick|last2=Hipes|first2=Patrick|date=2016-04-20|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> The premiere averaged over two million viewers,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-10-7-2016.html|title=UPDATED: SHOWBUZZDAILY\u2019s Top 150 Friday Cable Originals\u00a0& Network Finals: 10.7.2016 {{!}} Showbuzz Daily|website=www.showbuzzdaily.com|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> and had a mixed reception. In the same year, she appeared as Laina Michaels in the [[YouTube Premium]] film ''[[The Thinning]]'', starring alongside [[Logan Paul]] and [[Lia Marie Johnson]].<ref name=\":2\" /> In 2017, List appeared in the teen comedy film [[The Outcasts (2017 film)|''The Outcasts'']] as Mackenzie Smith.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/cannes-victoria-justice-starring-in-high-school-comedy-1201180198/|title=CANNES: Victoria Justice Starring in High-School Comedy|last=McNary|first=Dave|last2=McNary|first2=Dave|date=2014-05-14|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> Production had initially began in 2014 under its original title ''The Outskirts'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140809200534/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2014/07/06/madness-on-the-set-of-victoria-justice-and-eden-shers-movie-the-outskirts/|title=Madness On The Set Of Victoria Justice and Eden Sher\u2019s Movie \u201cThe Outskirts\u201d {{!}} Disney Dreaming|date=2014-08-09|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> and was not released until three years later. It was originally released [[direct-to-video]], but was eventually picked up for a theatrical release.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/swen-group-distribution-victoria-justice-outcasts-exclusive-1202004189/|title=Swen Group Moves Into U.S. Distribution With Victoria Justice\u2019s \u2018Outcasts\u2019 (EXCLUSIVE)|last=McNary|first=Dave|last2=McNary|first2=Dave|date=2017-03-08|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> The film was commercially unsuccessful.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=intl&id=outskirts2015.htm|title=Box Office Mojo|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, it was announced that List would leave the show, and depart from her work on Disney Channel entirely.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/will-smith-jada-pinkett-smith-dominate-top-actors-social-media-ranking-1138669/item/priyanka-chopra-mvp-9-5-1138571|title=6. Priyanka Chopra - Will Smith, Jada Pinkett Smith Dominate Top Actors Social Media Ranking|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2019/07/16/why-did-peyton-list-leave-bunkd-season-4-disney-channel/|title=Why did Peyton List leave Bunk'd? Disney actress has more in store!|last=Weston|first=Christopher|date=2019-07-16|website=HITC|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> When she still worked with the network, she was an active member of the [[Disney Channel Circle of Stars]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fanlala.com/news/26-disney-channel-stars-sing-do-you-want-build-snowman-frozen|title=26 Disney channel stars sing do you want build snowman frozen|date=July 18, 2014 |accessdate=July 28, 2014}}</ref> List reprised her role as Laina Michaels in ''[[The Thinning: New World Order]]'', the sequel to ''The Thinning'', which was released in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/films/2018/10/18/thinning-new-world-order-youtube-surprise-launches-shamed/|title=The Telegraph|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> In the same year, she starred alongside [[Asa Butterfield]] in the romantic drama film [[Then Came You (2018 film)|''Then Came You'']] as Ashley.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/then-came-you-trailer-asa-butterfield-maisie-williams-nina-dobrev-coming-of-age-1202520208/|title=\u2018Then Came You\u2019 Trailer: Asa Butterfield, Maisie Williams & Nina Dobrev In Coming-Of-Age Pic|last=Pedersen|first=Erik|last2=Pedersen|first2=Erik|date=2018-12-14|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> List was soon cast in the main role of Olivia Richmond in the first season of the [[supernatural]] [[web series]] [[Light as a Feather (TV series)|''Light as a Feather'']], which was released through [[Hulu]] on October 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/light-as-a-feather-cast-liana-liberato-haley-ramm-peyton-list-hulu-awesomenesstv-1202403357/|title=\u2018Light As A Feather\u2019 Cast Set: Liana Liberato, Haley Ramm, Peyton List, Others Join Hulu & AwesomenessTV Drama|last=Pedersen|first=Erik|last2=Pedersen|first2=Erik|date=2018-06-04|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> Also in 2018, she made her singing debut with the single \"Liar Liar\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Actress-Peyton-List-Drops-New-Pop-Anthem-LIAR-LIAR-20181102|title=Actress Peyton List Drops New Pop Anthem LIAR LIAR|last=Desk|first=BWW News|website=BroadwayWorld.com|accessdate=January 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, List voiced [[Barbara Gordon|Barbara Gordon / Batgirl]] in the direct-to-video [[superhero]] film [[Batman: Hush (film)|''Batman: Hush'']].<ref>{{Citation|title=Batman: Hush Movie - Exclusive First Look Photo and Voice Cast News - IGN|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/03/27/batman-hush-exclusive-first-look-photo-and-voice-cast-news|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> In the same year, she was cast in the recurring role of [[List of The Karate Kid characters|Tory]] in the YouTube Premium action series ''[[Cobra Kai]]'', which she played throughout the second season. List will next appear in the [[Music genre|musical]] film [[Valley Girl (2020 film)|''Valley Girl'']], a remake of the [[Valley Girl (1983 film)|1983 film]], which is slated for release in 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/06/valley-girl-peyton-list-mgm-1202106616/|title=MGM\u2019s \u2018Valley Girl\u2019 Remake Adds Peyton List|last=N'Duka|first=Amanda|last2=N'Duka|first2=Amanda|date=2017-06-02|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> She will also have a role in the upcoming direct-to-video film ''[[Hubie Halloween]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/adam-sandler-kevin-james-julie-bowen-maya-rudolph-netflix-comedy-1202650376/|title=Adam Sandler Sets Next Netflix Comedy With All-Star Cast Including Kevin James, Julie Bowen, Maya Rudolph & Many More|last=N'Duka|first=Amanda|last2=N'Duka|first2=Amanda|date=2019-07-22|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n==Namefellow==\nPeyton List shares the same name with a fellow actress, [[Peyton List (actress, born 1986)|Peyton List (born 1986)]].<ref name=\"saltman\">{{cite news |last1=Laura |first1=Saltman |title=A Tale Of Two Peytons: Jessie's Peyton List On Sharing Her Famous Name With Other Peyton List |url=https://www.yahoo.com/celebrity/news/tale-two-peytons-jessies-peyton-list-sharing-her-215829849.html |accessdate=November 20, 2019 |work=Access Hollywood |publisher=Yahoo News |date=October 14, 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170207024916/https://www.yahoo.com/celebrity/news/tale-two-peytons-jessies-peyton-list-sharing-her-215829849.html |archivedate=February 7, 2017}}</ref><ref name=nguyen>{{citation|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2016/10/peyton-list-frequency-swap-thinning-1201733445/|accessdate=November 29, 2016|work=[[IndieWire]]|title=Peyton List-icle: 6 Ways to Identify Which Peyton List Is Which|first=Hanh|last=Nguyen|date=October 5, 2016|quote='Peyton List is an American actress and model.' This Wikipedia description is accurate and true. The problem? It\u2019s true about two different people. That\u2019s right. Two Peyton Lists are working actresses and models. Two Peyton Lists are, um, listed on IMDb. Two Peyton Lists are currently on our TVs. Two Peyton Lists are confusing our Google searches. Two Peyton Lists are messing with our minds.}}</ref> The younger List was interviewed by ''[[Access Hollywood]]'', saying she uses '''Peyton R. List''' to avoid confusion.<ref name=saltman /> Union [[SAG-AFTRA]]'s policy avoids actors with the same name; this instance went unnoticed.<ref name=saltman/> They appeared in the same scene \u2014 when the older List starred on ''[[As the World Turns]]'' as Lucy Montgomery.<ref name=saltman /><ref name=\":1\">{{citation|url=http://heavy.com/entertainment/2016/10/peyton-list-disney-channel-star-bunkd-who-plays-emma-ross-the-swap-jessie-twin-brother-age-family-movies-photos/|accessdate=November 29, 2016|website=[[Heavy.com]]|title=Peyton List, Disney Channel Star: 5 Fast Facts You Need to Know|date=October 7, 2016|first=Daniel S.|last=Levine}}</ref> Years later, the younger List cited confusion when they stayed at the same hotel \u2014 they received [[daily call sheet]]s and [[voicemail]]s for each other.<ref name=saltman/> ''[[IndieWire]]'' noted the confusion appeared on the website [[Wikipedia]], where both actresses's articles started out with exactly the same introduction text of: \"Peyton List is an American actress and model.\"<ref name=nguyen/>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Film performances\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Spider-Man 2]]''\n| Little girl playing on steps\n| Uncredited<ref>{{cite web|title=The Cast of Disney's Jessie talk about swinging by Marvel's Ultimate Spider-Man|url=http://marvel.com/news/tv/23486/the_cast_of_disneys_jessie_talk_about_swinging_by_marvels_ultimate_spider-man_web-warriors|publisher=Marvel|accessdate=August 9, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[27 Dresses]]''\n| Young Jane Nichols\n|\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Confessions of a Shopaholic (film)|Confessions of a Shopaholic]]''\n| Shoestore girl #2\n|\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[3 Backyards]]''\n| Emily\n|\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Remember Me (2010 film)|Remember Me]]''\n| Samantha\n|\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''{{sortname|The|Sorcerer's Apprentice|dab=2010 film}}''\n| Young Becky\n|\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Bereavement (film)|Bereavement]]''\n| Wendy Miller\n|\n|-\n| 2011\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | ''[[Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Rodrick Rules (film)|Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Rodrick Rules]]''\n| Holly Hills\n|\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Something Borrowed (film)|Something Borrowed]]''\n| Young Darcy Rhone\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''{{sortname|The|Trouble with Cali}}''\n| Young Cali Bluejones\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Dog Days (film)|Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Dog Days]]''\n| Holly Hills\n| [[34th Young Artist Awards|Young Artist Award for Best Performance in a Feature Film&nbsp;\u2013 Young Ensemble Cast]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms34.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130403013454/http://www.youngartistawards.org/noms34.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=April 3, 2013 |title=34th Annual Young Artist Awards \u2013 Nominations |publisher=[[Young Artist Award]]s |accessdate=February 1, 2015 }}</ref>\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''{{sortname|The|Seventh Dwarf}}''\n| Princess Rose\n| Voice role\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[The Thinning]]''\n| Laina Michaels\n| <ref name=\":2\">{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2015/digital/news/logan-paul-peyton-list-the-thinning-legendary-1201643508/|title=Digital Star Logan Paul, Peyton List Topline \u2018The Thinning\u2019 Thriller from Legendary Digital (EXCLUSIVE)|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|last=Spangler|first=Todd|date=November 18, 2015|accessdate=February 14, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''{{sortname|The|Outcasts|dab=2017 film}}''\n| Mackenzie\n| Originally titled ''The Outskirts''; scheduled for a 2015 release, but held until 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/swen-group-distribution-victoria-justice-outcasts-exclusive-1202004189/|title=Swen Group Moves Into U.S. Distribution With Victoria Justice\u2019s \u2018Outcasts\u2019 (EXCLUSIVE)|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Dave|last=McNary|date=March 8, 2017|accessdate=March 8, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[The Thinning: New World Order]]''\n| Laina Michaels\n|\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Then Came You (2018 film)|Then Came You]]''\n| Ashley\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Batman: Hush (film)|Batman: Hush]]''\n| [[Barbara Gordon|Barbara Gordon / Batgirl]]\n| Voice role<ref>{{cite web |last1=Vejvoda |first1=Jim |title=Batman: Hush Movie - Exclusive First Look Photo and Voice Cast News |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/03/27/batman-hush-exclusive-first-look-photo-and-voice-cast-news |website=[[IGN]] |date=March 27, 2019 |accessdate=May 21, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Valley Girl (2020 film)|Valley Girl]]''\n| Courtney\n|Upcoming film<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/06/valley-girl-peyton-list-mgm-1202106616/|title=MGM\u2019s \u2018Valley Girl\u2019 Remake Adds Peyton List|last=N'Duka|first=Amanda|last2=N'Duka|first2=Amanda|date=June 2, 2017|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=July 17, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wildaboutmovies.com/2020_movies/valley-girl/|accessdate=November 27, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{TableTBA}}\n| ''[[Hubie Halloween]]''\n| {{TableTBA}}\n| Upcoming direct-to-video film<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/adam-sandler-kevin-james-julie-bowen-maya-rudolph-netflix-comedy-1202650376/|title=Adam Sandler Sets Next Netflix Comedy With All-Star Cast Including Kevin James, Julie Bowen, Maya Rudolph & Many More|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Amanda|last=N'Duka|date=July 22, 2019|access-date=July 22, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Television performances\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[As the World Turns]]''\n| Little girl in diner\n| Season 47, episode 143; uncredited<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|last=Saltman|first=Laura|title=A Tale Of Two Peytons: Jessie's Peyton List On Sharing Her Famous Name With Other Peyton List|url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/a-tale-of-two-peytons-jessies-peyton-list-on-sharing-her-famous-name-with-other-peyton-list_article_85502|work=Access Hollywood|date=October 14, 2013|accessdate=March 18, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[All My Children]]''\n| Bess\n| Season 35, episode 229\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Late Show with David Letterman]]''\n| Young tourist at the [[Paul Shaffer]] hotel\n| Season 12, episode 194\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''\n| Little girl\n| Episode: \"LeBron James/Kanye West\"; uncredited{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Cashmere Mafia]]''\n| Sasha Burden\n| 4 episodes\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Wonder Pets]]''\n| Piglet #1 / chick #1\n| Voice role; episode: \"Kalamazoo\"\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Late Show with David Letterman''\n| [[Von Trapp Children|Von Trapp kid]]\n| Season 15, episode 73; uncredited{{citation needed|date=March 2017}}\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Gossip Girl]]''\n| Little girl #1\n| Episode: \"[[Enough About Eve]]\"\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Secrets in the Walls]]''\n| Molly Easton\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]''\n| Young Larissa Welsh\n| Episode: \"Possessed\"\n|-\n| 2011\u20132015\n| ''[[Jessie (2011 TV series)|Jessie]]''\n| Emma Ross\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''{{sortname|The|Dog Who Saved the Holidays|nolink=1}}''\n| Eve\n| Voice role; television film\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Austin & Ally]]''\n| Emma Ross\n| Episode: \"[[Austin & Jessie & Ally All Star New Year]]\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''{{sortname|A|Sister's Nightmare|nolink=1}}''\n| Emily Ryder\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2013\u20132014\n| ''[[Pass the Plate]]''\n| Herself\n| Co-host; seasons 3\u20134\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[I Didn't Do It (TV series)|I Didn't Do It]]''\n| Sherri\n| Episode: \"Dance Fever\"\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Ultimate Spider-Man (TV seri